Gareth Southgate is confident Saido Berahino is ready to recapture the form that made him one of England’s rising stars.

Berahino was catapulted into the limelight just a year ago by scoring a hat-trick on his full debut for West Bromwich Albion in a League Cup tie with Newport. He then fired the opening goal of Southgate’s reign as England Under 21 head coach.

Berahino was soon being talked about as a potential wildcard for the World Cup finals, as his hot streak continued with six goals in his first four Under 21 appearances and, notably, the winner against Manchester United at Old Trafford last September.

