The campaign ended with problems, however. He was filmed inhaling the legal high ‘hippy crack’ after a dressing-room row with Albion colleague James Morrison but Southgate is confident Berahino is ready to resume his progress.

‘I think he was slightly affected when the manager (Steve Clarke), who he had a good relationship with, left,’ said Southgate, whose side face Lithuania in a Euro 2015 qualifier tomorrow.

‘All the reports we have had have been good — he came back early and in really good shape for pre-season — and he’s started the season really well.

‘The great thing with Saido is that he recognises he has had a dip and then done something about it. We don’t batter them for making mistakes.’

